Malachite practically drags Polaris over to the shop and opens the door, gesturing for him to go in.

“Ah—“
He lets himself get dragged in, a little nervous.

"I'm glad you're letting me do this,"
He purrs, taking his hand as he surveys lip glosses.
“I don’t exactly have a choice in the matter..” he murmurs, looking around at all the makeup, ignoring the looks hes getting from the employees.
(what if 👀 we robbed a mun Sephora together 👉👈😳😳😳 (and we were both boys 🙈))
((he will NOT commit crimes

"It'll be nice,"
He stands on tip-toe and pecks him on the cheek, still a little giddy that he's finally able to be affectionate with him in public like this.
"It's for the wedding."

Sighing, he looks at Malachite with soft eyes. “Yeah, I get it.”
*Not a fan of the store employees, though..* he thinks, sensitive to the thoughts of others as he remembers that he can do that now.
"Do you want to just get the stuff and then let me do it at home? Or do you want to go ahead and do it here?"
He shrugs. “I don’t care where you do it. I don’t know much about makeup, but wouldn’t it be good to try stuff first before buying it?” *Since that’s how it works with buying most stuff..*

"Mhm... alright,"
He picks up a metallic eyeshadow pallette and examines it.
He places his head on Malachite’s shoulder, peering over it and tuning out the thoughts of others. “What’s that?”

"Eyeshadow."
He opens the case and smudges a finger through the powder, showing it to Polaris.
“Huh. Looks... sparkly.”
"Mhm. Do you like it?"
He nods. “It looks nice.”
He seems to have forgotten that that’s going on his face.

"I think it'll suit you,"
He hums and closes the case, peering at some mascara.
“Oh,” he pipes, finally remembering. “Uh. Should I find somewhere to sit down? It’d be hard to put stuff on with my height..”
"Yeah, there's a bench over there. You trust me to pick stuff out?"

He nods. “Sure.” *Not like I’d know what I was doing if I chose stuff, anyways.*
“I’ll go sit down,” he says, pointing to the bench and walking over there.

"Alright,"
He spends a few more minutes picking out products, before paying and setting them down on the counter.
"I got a few things. Tell me if you hate any of it, okay?"

He nods, humming, still avoiding the gazes of the girls looking at him. With all this staying at home again, he kinda forgot that he’s 1. 14’7 and 2... Jotaro’s mun.
*I probably won’t hate it since he picked it out for me.*

"Here, can you look up for me?"
He cups his chin and tilts his face up, turning it toward the light.
He swallows, trying to nod but realizing he probably shouldnt, tilting his head up slightly.

He smiles down at him, turning his head back and forth.
"I'm going to start out with eyeliner. It's going to be near your eye, but I'll be careful, okay?"

“Mhm.”
*My.. eyes..*
He starts to feel hyper aware of his scars, the cracks in his skin glowing a little. He shoves down the glowing.

"You're so pretty..."
He leans down to kiss his forehead, then takes the cap off of the pencil. 
"Hold still."
He hums again, letting out a shaky breath. It really shouldn’t be this hard to *not* be conscious, but right now, especially with Malachite so close to his face.. he can’t exactly just help it.

He sticks his tongue out, lightly sketching the shape on with bated breath.
"...Alright,"
He sighs,
"That's one eye done. Wanna see?"
“Uh. Sure. Can I open my eye?” he asks, not really sure if he should. It feels a bit... *weird* on his lid.
"Mhm."
He cracks open an eye, nervously looking around for a second while his eyes adjust to the light again. “Feels.. weird. Like dust.”
"Yeah, it takes a while to get used to it. Do you like the way it looks?"
((did he do it over the side w/ the vertical scar or the star?
(star)

Looking in the mirror, he.. doesn’t know how to feel. For a second, he forgot about that *thing* on his face. Why now? Why did he hate it *now?* He never cared about it before, but looking at it now feels like someone stabbing him in the damn gut. The skin almost feels *itchy* with the makeup on, and he just...
“It looks nice. Thank you.”

"...Are you okay?"
Malachite may not be psychic, but he knows Polaris well enough to know he's upset about something.
He nods. “Mhm. It feels weird, but it looks nice.”

He furrows his brow, still not convinced, but lets it go.
"...Ready for me to do your other eye?"

“..How?”
It’s not exactly like he has a whole eyelid...
"I'll just do the part that's there. You okay?"

“Mhm.”
He’s a bit nervous.. It’ll probably be difficult to actually do much makeup at all on a half—scarred eyelid, but he trusts Malachite. So, he closes his eyes again.

"Remember, I have scars over *both* of my eyes. I know what I'm doing"
He works on the other one, applying it as gently as possible.
“Your scars are thin,” he retorts, struggling not to arch his brows against the feeling n his lid.

"...They're still there. I've gotta be careful, or it slips into it and I have to clean the pencil off."
He finishes, pulling away again.
"Mmmm... it looks nice, I think."

He sticks out his tongue. “Gross.”
He opens his eyes, not feeling nearly as bad about the vertical scar. There’s still pain there, yeah, but.. it’s not as bad. “It looks.. better than expected. I didn’t think makeup would work on me.”
*"Anything* would work on you, I keep telling you that."
He shrugs. “Yeah, well, you love me. So there’s bias.”

"Have you ever seen me soften a blow in regards to someone's appearance? You've been stunning since I first saw you,"
He purrs.

“Like I said, you love me. That’s why,” he says, turning around and giving Malachite a little kiss. He hears the disappointment in the thoughts of some of the employees around him and remembers that they’re in public. He hurries himself out of the kiss and shoves down the urge to cough. “Y-You wanted to apply, uh... shadow? Stuff?”

"Only a little bit. Here, close your eyes again."
He loads some of the powder onto a brush, tapping off the excess.

“Kay.”
He closes his eyes again, still feeling nervous. He feels.. *vulnerable* keeping his eyes shut. If someone were to attack, he’d sense them, but he wouldn’t see them.

He dabs some of the shimmery makeup onto his eyelids, making sure to keep it light. He promised it would be subtle. 
"And... there. Is this good?"

He opens his eyes again a bit, before shutting them again. It feels kinda itchy when his lids fold...
“It feels weird.”
"I can brush some off, if you want."
“Hm. Do you have any that isn’t, uh, glittery?”
"Yeah, sure. Maybe something green, to match your outfit? Or red, to match mine?"
“I think red would be good,” he says, nodding.

"Mhm... it's kinda pink, to make it clash less."
He brushes some of the gold off and starts adding the new color, humming softly. Polaris is *beautiful*, and he pauses for a moment to just... look at him.
"...You look nice."
“Thanks. I can’t see you, but you do, too,” he responds, trying to not tense up from the feeling of Malachite pausing.

He lets out a pleased purr.
"I'm done with your eyes, do you wanna look now?"

He nods, opening his eyes a little.
He looks... different. It’s new. “It looks good. I’m not sure what it exactly added, though..”
"It's part of dressing up. We're wearing nice clothes, this is the same thing."

“I.. guess..”
He’s trying *so damn hard* to ignore his scar. The light red matches really well with it, but it just reminds him more of how much it’s just.. *there.* Why does it hurt so bad?
“Hey, Mala..?”
"Mhm?"
“Has— Have you.. Was there ever a time where you knew me when my scar wasn’t here?”
(was there?)
((nah, the scar happened *way* before they met
"Mm, no, it's been there as long as I can remember."

“...”
He stays quiet for a moment. “I... It’s.. It’s easy to notice, I think. I mean—“
He’s stumbling on his words, not sure how to form the sentence. “It.. Stands out right now, to me.”

He's... insecure?
"...Are you upset about it?"

“I... don’t know...” 
He’s not sure if it’s... *sadness* he feels towards it? It’s hard to explain. Like a mix between regret and embarrassment, like it’s something he regrets happening. But he doesn’t even know what happened. Why is he feeling this way..?
He’s beginning to silently panic.

"Hey-"
*Shit.*
"Hey, Polaris, what's wrong? Do you want to take the makeup off?"
“N-No, it’s fine. I’m fine. Are there wipes anywhere?”

"Mhm,"
He hands him some wipes, concerned.
"...You don't seem fine."
He mumbles a small thanks, wiping off the makeup, trying to avoid getting the wipe in his deep scar. “I think I’m just tired. Are the girls still in the mall?”
"I think so. Do you want to go home?"

He nods. They got what they needed, anyways. 
Wait.
“Where’s the bags of clothes we got?”

"Hierophant has them."
It waves.

He waves back, keeping his face blank.
“O-Okay.. We should say bye to them.”

"Mhm..."
Something's *fucky*. He's not gonna push it now, but he'll get Polaris to talk later.
*That’s a way to describe this feeling,* he thinks to himself, sighing. He stands up, heading towards the door. “Let’s go.”
He nods, taking his hand and giving it a reassuring squeeze.
